data.title: Dr. Edward O'Brien, Psy.D.
data.text: I graduated Drew University,New York University, and Southern California University. Employment was with New York State Education Dept in N.Y.C. as a vocational rehab counselor in a Mental Health unit. I then was the base psychologist and Deputy Director of Family Services for the USN in Bermuda till late 1990. In 1996 I started teaching at the college as an adjunct. I am a licensened Mental Health Counselor and NCC. Outside activities are bridge(life/master);sailing; ham radio, and family activities. My teaching philosophy is keep in relavent and interesting.
